idCitation.resTitle: Parcel data for Plympton, MA, complying with Level 3 of MassGIS digital parcel standard

dataIdInfo.idPurp: M240TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Plympton that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M240Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M240OthLeg and M240Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure, this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Assessor's parcel data for Town of Plympton, MA. Developed from tax maps. Last updated by CGIS Mapping, LLC 6/26/2025.
